<item>
            <title>[LU-7025] lfsck_layout_scan_stripes suspicious rc assignment</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7025</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We seem to be having this sort of code there:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (lso == NULL) {
                        struct lu_attr *attr = &amp;amp;info-&amp;gt;lti_la;

                        rc = dt_attr_get(env, parent, attr);
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rc != 0) {
                                rc = PTR_ERR(lso);
                                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;goto&lt;/span&gt; next;
                        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now note that lso is already NULL - meaning we reset nonzero rc into zero in quite a roundabout way.&lt;br/&gt;
Are you sure this is what was desired? I think we should just reuse the rc with the error instead?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
